Bristol Panel Signal Box was built on the site of the Platform 14 after it closed. When opened it controlled 280 multiple-aspect signals and 243 motor-worked points on {{convert|114|mi|km}} of routes around Bristol, the largest area controlled by a single signal box on [[British Rail]] at the time.<ref>{{cite journal| last = Kitchenside| first = GM| title = The Bristol resignalling scheme controls the crossroads of the West| journal = Modern Railways| volume = 30| issue = 292| pages = 10<U+2013>15| publisher = Ian Allan| date = 1973| accessdate = }}</ref>

