===Bus and ferry links===
[[Image:Temple Meads Bristol Airport Flyer 23021.jpg|thumb|right|The [[Bristol International Airport|Bristol International]] Flyer picking up outside the station]]
In addition to its train services, Temple Meads is served by many [[bus]]es. [[First Bristol]] services 8, 8A, 9 and 9A provide a frequent service from in front of the station doors to the City Centre, [[Clifton, Bristol|Clifton]], [[Bristol Zoo]], and Redland.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.firstgroup.com/ukbus/southwest/bristol/timetables/index.php|title=First Bristol Timetable 8, 8A, 9 and 9A|work=First Group|accessdate=2008-07-04}}</ref> Other services calling at the Station Approach bus stops are 330 and 331 to [[Bristol International Airport]], and 121, 672 and 674 which serve the airport and then continue to various [[Mendip Hills|Mendips]] villages such as [[Wrington]], [[Winscombe]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.firstgroup.com/ukbus/southwest/bristol/timetables/index.php|title=First Somerset & Avon Timetable 121|work=First Group|accessdate=2008-07-04}}</ref> and [[Cheddar]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bathnes.gov.uk/BathNES/transportandstreets/travel/buses/SupportedServices/|title=Bath & North East Somerset bus timetable 672/674|publisher=B&NES|accessdate=2008-07-04}}</ref>

On Temple Way, the main road outside the station, are bus stops for country services to [[Wells, Somerset|Wells]] and [[Bath, Somerset|Bath]] via [[Saltford]]. On the opposite side of the road a bus stop is served by frequent city services 1 (from [[Brislington East|Broomhill]] to [[Westbury-on-Trym]] and [[Cribbs Causeway]]), and 54 (from Stockwood to [[Southmead]] and Cribbs Causeway).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.firstgroup.com/ukbus/southwest/bristol/map/bristol.php|title=First Bristol network maps|work=First Group|accessdate=2008-07-04}}</ref>

The [[Bristol Ferry Boat]] calls at a landing stage in the [[Bristol Harbour|Floating Harbour]] outside the station on a route to [[Bristol Bridge]], St Augustine's Reach in the City Centre, the [[SS Great Britain]], and [[Hotwells]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bristolferry.com/page.php?xPage=timetable_temple.html|title=Bristol Ferry Boat Company <U+2013> Temple Meads timetable|work=Temple Meads timetable|publisher=Bristol Ferry Boat Company |accessdate=2008-07-04}}</ref>

